  "description": "Thinking how to handle multiple cosmos in GnoponEmacs In my last babble, I posed the question to myself, how would I organize my files if they were themselves the \u0026ldquo;dimension\u0026rdquo; part of a MUD - that is, the library, in the classic engine/library split.\nBut the difference is that we might have data files that are Org-mode at their core, but tangle out Python and LISP\u0026hellip;\n\u0026hellip;I\u0026rsquo;m actually being distracted by my family as I try and write this - which isn\u0026rsquo;t a complaint! But it\u0026rsquo;s making it hard to build the sequence of thoughts I\u0026rsquo;m trying to convey to myself.\n",
